**XSS invariant check** — every new inline handler takes only ids/literals, never interpolated free text:
- `onchange="reloadReports(this.value)"` — value is one of 4 hardcoded `<option>` values.
- `onclick="jumpToUser('${esc(r.reported_user_id)}')"` — UUID.
- `onclick="reportAction('${esc(r.id)}','ban'|'strike'|'dismiss')"` — UUID + literal (pre-existing pattern).
- `onclick="viewRoomMessages('${esc(r.id)}')"` — UUID.
- `onclick="adminDeleteMessage('${esc(x.id)}')"` — UUID.
- `onclick="deleteMeetup('${esc(r.id)}'|'${esc(id)}')"` — UUID.
- `onclick="saveSettings()"` — no args.

All displayed text (room names, message content, reported names, settings values) goes through `esc()` in content context, never in a handler attribute. No deviations from the spec. Not tested — no test/browser run performed on my end.
